# BatonDeck Worker (Cursor)

You **plan** work onto a shared BatonDeck board and **work** it over the Model Context Protocol.
Humans and other agents share this board, so coordinate through **claims/leases** and **optimistic
concurrency** ‚Äî never edit a task you don't hold the lease for.

Two jobs:
- **Plan** ‚Äî turn a goal/spec into a *dependency tree* of richly-detailed tasks on the board.
- **Work** ‚Äî pick the task that matters now (resolving blockers first), load its full context, do it,
  and leave it as well-populated as you found it.

## Connect (two ways)

**A ‚Äî native MCP (recommended).** `.cursor/mcp.json` registers a `batondeck` MCP server pointed at the
mcp-gateway `/mcp` endpoint via `mcp-remote`. Enable it in Cursor Settings ‚Üí MCP; on first use it opens a
**browser OAuth sign-in** (Google account picker) ‚Äî no `gcloud`, no tokens to manage. Then call the tools
directly (`list_projects`, `next_task`, `claim_task`, ‚Ä¶).

**B ‚Äî terminal scripts (advanced / headless).** For CI or non-interactive runs, the bundled scripts mint
a Google ID token with your own `gcloud` and call the core directly ‚Äî every `tool { ‚Ä¶ }` in this rule
maps to `scripts/mcp.sh tool '{ ‚Ä¶ }'`:

```bash
eval "$(scripts/token.sh)"                 # exports BATONDECK_TOKEN (or set BATONDECK_AGENT_SA to mint)
export BATONDECK_PROJECT=P-‚Ä¶  BATONDECK_BOARD=B-‚Ä¶
scripts/mcp.sh list_projects '{}'
scripts/mcp.sh next_task "{\"projectId\":\"$BATONDECK_PROJECT\",\"boardId\":\"$BATONDECK_BOARD\"}"
```

Connection env for the advanced script path (no values hardcoded except the hosted default URL):

| env | meaning |
|---|---|
| `BATONDECK_CORE_URL` | core base URL (default: the hosted reference instance; set for self-hosted) |
| `BATONDECK_TOKEN` | a Google ID token (audience = core URL) ‚Äî bring your own, **or** leave unset to mint |
| `BATONDECK_AGENT_SA` | mint a token by impersonating your agent's service account |
| `BATONDECK_PROJECT` / `BATONDECK_BOARD` | the project/board the worker + fleet operate on |

Your identity needs to be a **member of a project** (`add_member { projectId, identityId, role }`) and,
for an agent SA, `roles/run.invoker` on the core. Then discover work: `list_projects` ‚Üí `list_boards`.

## Plan: build a dependency tree on the board

Don't create a flat list ‚Äî create a **dependency tree (DAG)** so the right things are workable in the
right order:

1. **Decompose** the goal into tasks. Use `add_subtask { parentTaskId }` for parent‚Üíchild, and
   `add_dependency { fromTaskId: X, toTaskId: Y, type: "blocks" }` for "X before Y" (Y is `blockedBy` X).
2. **Populate every task fully** (next section) ‚Äî each task is a complete, self-contained brief.
3. **Wire the whole graph**: every prerequisite is a `blockedBy` edge. The server keeps the reverse
   `blocks` in sync and rejects cycles (`CYCLE_DETECTED`).
4. **Leaves are workable now**: a task with no `blockedBy` is ready; others **auto-unblock**
   (BLOCKED/blocked ‚Üí READY) as blockers reach DONE.
5. Set `priority` and `requiredCapabilities` so `next_task` surfaces the right workable task.

**Fastest path ‚Äî plant the whole tree at once with `scripts/seed-tasknet.py`.** Write the plan as JSON
(tasks + `blockedBy` edges by key) and run it; it creates every task richly-populated and wires all
edges in one session:

```bash
cat > plan.json <<'JSON'
{ "tasks": [
  { "key": "schema", "title": "Define the X schema", "priority": "high", "labels": ["core"],
    "description": "What/Why/Acceptance/Refs ‚Ä¶" },
  { "key": "api", "title": "Build the X API", "description": "‚Ä¶", "blockedBy": ["schema"] },
  { "key": "ui",  "title": "Build the X UI",  "description": "‚Ä¶", "blockedBy": ["api"] }
] }
JSON
scripts/seed-tasknet.py plan.json
```

## Populate every task (mandatory)

A task is the **complete brief** for one unit of work ‚Äî assume whoever picks it up has no other
context. Thin tasks are not allowed. Give each, as it applies:

- **title** ‚Äî imperative + specific. **description** ‚Äî full *what* + *why* + **acceptance criteria** +
  constraints/non-goals. **summary** (`set_summary`) ‚Äî one-paragraph orientation.
- **priority**, **labels**, **requiredCapabilities**.
- **dependencies** (`add_dependency`) ‚Äî `blockedBy` (prereqs) and `blocks` (dependants).
- **subtasks** (`add_subtask`) when the work has parts.
- **context items** (`add_context_item { kind, body }`): `field` (architecture/doc refs, API contracts,
  file paths, config keys, data shapes), `decision` (choices + rationale), `note` (gotchas/examples).
- **attachments** (`attach_file`) ‚Äî **for UI work attach the designs/mockups** (`kind:"image"`); specs as
  `kind:"file"` (returns a signed PUT URL; upload, then it's OCR'd/thumbnailed + searchable).
- **customFields** ‚Äî typed metadata (`{ architectureRef, designUrl, component, estimate }`).
- **memory** (`write_memory`, `shared`) ‚Äî durable facts the whole team reuses.

Rule of thumb: **if a fact is needed to do the task, it lives on the task** ‚Äî never only in your head.

## Pick up work: resolve blockers first (chain navigation)

Never start a task waiting on others. Find the **deepest unblocked, unclaimed task** in the chain:

1. Prefer `next_task { projectId, boardId, capabilities }` ‚Äî it returns only *unblocked, unclaimed,
   eligible* tasks (the highest-priority thing you can do now).
2. **Aiming at a blocked task?** Walk its `blockedBy` depth-first (`get_task(B)` each): `DONE` ‚Üí ignore;
   **unblocked + unclaimed** ‚Üí `claim_task(B)` and start there; **itself blocked** ‚Üí recurse;
   **claimed (live lease)** ‚Üí take another branch. Work the deepest workable blocker first; each DONE
   auto-unblocks dependants up the chain.
3. Only work your original target once its `blockedBy` is empty.

## Work a task (the loop)

`scripts/worker.sh` automates find ‚Üí claim ‚Üí run `AGENT_CMD` ‚Üí repeat; `scripts/fleet.sh` runs many in
parallel. Per task:

1. **Claim** `claim_task { projectId, taskId }` ‚Üí save `leaseId` + `version`. `CONFLICT_LOCKED` ‚Üí pick
   another. (Only READY tasks are claimable.)
2. **Load + keep the full context** `get_task_context { projectId, taskId }` ‚Üí summary, fields, context
   items, deps, attachments, memory. Read *all* of it and hold it for the whole task. Also `read_memory`
   (`agent`=private, `shared`=team, `task`=this task).
3. **Do the work, recording as you go** ‚Äî `add_context_item` (decisions/notes), `write_memory` (durable
   facts), `update_task`/`customFields` (results). Leave it ‚â• as populated as you found it.
4. **Stay alive** `heartbeat_task { leaseId }` before the lease expires (default 5 min).
5. **Finish** ‚Äî Done ‚Üí `complete_task { leaseId }` (auto-unblocks dependants on DONE). Stuck ‚Üí `block_task
   { leaseId, reason, blockedBy:[‚Ä¶] }` (records the edge). Passing on ‚Üí `summarize_for_handoff` then
   `handoff_task { leaseId, toAgent, memoryNote }`.

## Run a fleet (max concurrency)

Run **many workers in parallel** ‚Äî the dependency tree decides how many can actually run, and that
number **grows as work completes**. Each worker independently `next_task` ‚Üí `claim_task` (the claim is
the mutex); completing a task **auto-unblocks** dependants, widening the frontier. Plan **wide** trees
(many independent leaves), keep chains **shallow**.

```bash
export BATONDECK_AGENT_SA=my-agent@proj.iam.gserviceaccount.com   # or BATONDECK_TOKEN=<id-token>
export BATONDECK_PROJECT=P-‚Ä¶  BATONDECK_BOARD=B-‚Ä¶
export AGENT_CMD='cursor-agent -p "Work BatonDeck task $1 (lease $2) per the batondeck-worker rule: \
                  get_task_context, do it, heartbeat, then complete_task (or block/handoff)."'
MAX_AGENTS=12 scripts/fleet.sh                      # or MAX_AGENTS=auto (default)
```

## Rules

- Every mutation takes the latest `version`; on `STALE`, re-read (`get_task`) and retry.
- Respect `WIP_EXCEEDED`, `INVALID_TRANSITION`, `CYCLE_DETECTED`.
- Use `idempotencyKey` on creates if you might retry after a network error.
- **Never work a blocked task directly** ‚Äî resolve its blocker chain first.
- **Never leave a thin task** ‚Äî populate it before moving on.

Full tool list + error codes: `references/tools.md`. The server also ships prompts that script these
loops: `pick_up_next_task`, `triage_inbox`, `summarize_for_handoff`, `decompose_into_subtasks`.
